<!--
  iOS FLAVOR SETUP — MUST BE DONE MANUALLY IN XCODE
  ==================================================
  Android flavors are configured via build.gradle.kts productFlavors (see android/app/build.gradle.kts).
  iOS flavor equivalents require manual Xcode setup. Do NOT edit project.pbxproj by hand.

  Steps to add a new flavor (e.g. "facundo"):
  1. In Xcode, open Runner.xcworkspace.
  2. Duplicate the "Runner" scheme (Product > Scheme > Manage Schemes > Duplicate).
     Name the new scheme "facundo".
  3. In the scheme's Build Settings, set the following per scheme:
       PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER  = com.facundo.ligafutbol   (placeholder — confirm with client)
       DISPLAY_NAME               = Liga Facundo              (placeholder — confirm with client)
  4. Create ios/Flutter/facundo.xcconfig with:
       #include "Generated.xcconfig"
       PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER=com.facundo.ligafutbol
       FLUTTER_TARGET=lib/main_facundo.dart
  5. Assign the xcconfig to the facundo scheme's Debug and Release configurations.
  6. If Firebase push notifications are per-tenant, place the tenant-specific
     GoogleService-Info.plist under ios/Runner/<flavor>/GoogleService-Info.plist
     and wire it via a Run Script build phase that copies the right file.

  Existing Marianista values (tenant zero — DO NOT CHANGE):
    PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER = com.andrescampos.torneochaminade   (from pbxproj)
    DISPLAY_NAME               = Torneo Chami                       (current CFBundleDisplayName)
    Firebase project: shared with Facundo until separate Firebase projects are provisioned.

  Run command for Facundo flavor:
    flutter run --flavor facundo -t lib/main_facundo.dart
    flutter build ipa --flavor facundo -t lib/main_facundo.dart
-->
<plist version="1.0">
	<dict>
		<key>ITSAppUsesNonExemptEncryption</key>
		<false/>
		<key>CADisableMinimumFrameDurationOnPhone</key>
		<true/>
		<key>CFBundleDevelopmentRegion</key>
		<string>$(DEVELOPMENT_LANGUAGE)</string>
		<key>CFBundleDisplayName</key>
		<string>Torneo Chami</string>
